history.content: Usually advisors (especially if they're not the CS advisors) will advise you to Phase I the classes most important to you without thinking of Phase I/Phase II and what would be most advantageous to you to sign up for in which phase. I'd personally say that everyone that I know that's phase 2'ed 61B has usually gotten into the class (also because in the fall it's not as demanded as it is in the spring) and so you should also likely be fine to phase 2.
Agree with student. Phase I what you absolutely need; however the class has historically been large enough to accommodate phase II folks who are flexible

I currently have not enrolled in 61b for phase 1 and I was planning on enrolling during phase 2. However, after talking to an L&S adviser, she recommended that I drop another one of my classes and sign up for 61b first, as I am trying to declare CS.

Will I be able to get into 61B if I sign up during phase 2? Or is it best to switch one of my classes now?
history.subject: CS 61B Phase 1?
